import/no-empty-named-blocks

ðŸ”§ðŸ’¡ This rule is automatically fixable by the --fix CLI option and manually fixable by editor suggestions.

Reports the use of empty named import blocks.

Rule Details

Valid

import { mod } from 'mod'
import Default, { mod } from 'mod'

When using typescript

import type { mod } from 'mod'

When using flow

import typeof { mod } from 'mod'

Invalid

import {} from 'mod'
import Default, {} from 'mod'

When using typescript

import type Default, {} from 'mod'
import type {} from 'mod'

When using flow

import typeof {} from 'mod'
import typeof Default, {} from 'mod'
